title: Caitlyn Jenner is going on a speaking tour
text:
By Liz Raftery, Now that the first season of I Am Cait has wrapped, don't expect Caitlyn Jenner to kick back and take it easy.
Jenner, 65, will embark on a five-city speaking tour next year with Unique Lives & Experiences, a company that organizes women's lectures across the United States and Canada, People reports. The reality star and former Olympian's tour, called "Up Close and Personal," kicks off on Feb. 22, 2016 in Toronto and will make additional stops in Vancouver, Denver, San Francisco and Seattle. Tickets are already on sale and range from $40 to a $500 VIP package.
Why I Am Cait is worth watching, even if you're not a Kardashian fan
Since coming out as transgender publicly earlier this year, Jenner spoke at the ESPYs , where she was the recipient of the Arthur Ashe Courage Award.
Tickets and additional information for the "Up Close and Personal" tour are available here .
